5:43; Luke 23:50; John 19:38), who took Jesus down from the Cross, wrapped him in a shroud, and buried him in a rock tomb. According to medieval legend, Joseph of Arimathea brought the Holy Grail to Britain. The name was uncommon in Britain in the Middle Ages but was revived in the mid 16th century and had become popular by the 1630s, remaining so ever since."],"variants":[{"name":"Josef","meanings":[", Dutch, Scandinavian, and Czech spelling of   Joseph  , now also in use in the English‐speaking world."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705201,"age":59,"year":"1549","julianDay":2286821,"title":"Book of Common Prayer","description":"Book of Common Prayer, a product of the English Reformation, was published in 1549 for assistance in the administration of the sacraments and other rites and ceremonies of the church according to the use of the Church of England. The book outlined morning, evening, and communion prayers and orders for baptism and marriage, thus making England a truly Protestant state.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Book_of_Common_Prayer","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Book of Common Prayer","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705202,"age":68,"year":"1558","julianDay":2290108,"title":"Act of Uniformity","description":"The Act of Uniformity was passed by the Parliament of England and required all people to go to church once a week. The consequence of not attending church was a fine of 12 pence, which was a considerable amount for a poor person.","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705205,"age":79,"year":"1569","julianDay":2294126,"title":"State Lottery","description":"A State Lottery was recorded in 1569. The tickets were sold at St. Paul's Cathedral in London.","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705207,"age":95,"year":"1585","julianDay":2299970,"title":"The First English Colony is Established in America","description":"England established its first colony in North America in 1585 as a way to generate additional wealth. The colony was named Virginia, after the virgin Queen Elizabeth I.","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705208,"age":97,"year":"1587","julianDay":2300700,"title":"Elizabeth I Signs Death Warrant for Mary, Queen of Scots","description":"Elizabeth I signed the death warrant for Mary, Queen of Scots, on February 1, 1587, as she was found guilty of plotting to assasinate Elizabeth. Mary, Queen of Scots, was beheaded at Fotheringhay Castle in England on February 8, 1587.","url":"https://www.elizabethi.org/mary_queen_of_scots/","urlTitle":"Elizabeth I.org - Mary Queen of Scots","jurisdictionLevel":0}],"lifeSummary":"Joseph Grundy was born in 1490, in England. He married Frederica Smith in 1510, in England. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter."},"et":{"1490–":"1490–Surnud","1493–Female":"1493–Surnud","1545–1598":"1545–1598","1490–Male":"1490–Surnud","1569":"1569","1558":"1558","1545":"1545","1510":"1510","1587":"1587","1598":"1598","1585":"1585","Abt 1545":"umbes 1545","1493":"1493","1490":"1490","1549":"1549","Little Eversden, Cambridgeshire, England":"Little Eversden, Cambridgeshire, England","England":"England"},"fi":{"1490–":"1490–Kuollut","1493–Female":"1493–Kuollut","1545–1598":"1545–1598","1490–Male":"1490–Kuollut","1569":"1569","1558":"1558","1545":"1545","1510":"1510","1587":"1587","1598":"1598","1585":"1585","Abt 1545":"noin 1545","1493":"1493","1490":"1490","1549":"1549","Little Eversden, Cambridgeshire, England":"Little Eversden, Cambridgeshire, England","England":"England"},"fr":{"1490–":"1490–Décédé","1493–Female":"1493–Décédée","1545–1598":"1545–1598","1490–Male":"1490–Décédé","1569":"1569","1558":"1558","1545":"1545","1510":"1510","1587":"1587","1598":"1598","1585":"1585","Abt 1545":"environ 1545","1493":"1493","1490":"1490","1549":"1549","Little Eversden, Cambridgeshire, England":"Little Eversden, Cambridgeshire, Angleterre","England":"Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Joseph Grundy est né en 1490, à Angleterre. Il a épousé Frederica Smith en 1510, à Angleterre. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fille."},"de":{"1490–":"1490–Ver